obo:GO_0098978  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2810  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 3: \"Fz5 stimulates the formation of presynaptic sites\"\n- \"Axonal Fz5 expression induces a 78% and a 36% increase in the number of synapsin I and bassoon puncta, respectively (Fig. 3C,D). Thus, expression of Fz5 in axons induces presynaptic differentiation in a similar manner to the synaptogenic factor Wnt7a.\"\n\nFig.4: \"Fz5 promotes synapse formation by binding to Wnt7a\"\n- \"Therefore, Fz5CRD completely blocks the synaptogenic activity of Wnt7a, suggesting that Fz5 mediates Wnt7a function at synapses.\"\n- \"In hippocampal neurons, the Fz5 shRNA mixture significantly decreased the level of endogenous Fz5, whereas nc-shRNA had no effect (Fig. 5C).\"\n\nFig.5: \"Fz5 knockdown abolishes Wnt7a-induced synapse formation\". Experimental description: - \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) Sprague-Dawley rat embryos ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2810" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

